<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[192,1440,291,443]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,317,291,315]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Remarks</emphasis>
. The dorsal color pattern of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon &amp; González" authorityYear="2011" box="[670,837,291,315]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humboldti">
<emphasis box="[670,692,292,315]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[708,837,291,315]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">humboldti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique, not resembling that of any previously described species. It will key to 
<taxonomicName box="[590,726,323,347]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brethesi">
<emphasis box="[590,612,324,347]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[628,726,323,347]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">brethesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, couplet 47, in 
<bibRefCitation author="Gordon, R. D. &amp; C. Canepari" box="[919,1278,323,347]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="245 - 512" refId="ref7630" refString="Gordon, R. D., and C. Canepari. 2008. South American Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), Part XI: a systematic revision of Hyperaspidini (Hyperaspidinae). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot; XCIX: 245 - 512." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gordon and Canepari (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, which has a different dorsal pattern and male genitalia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[192,1440,291,443]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
The 
<typeStatus box="[295,401,387,411]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon &amp; González" authorityYear="2011" box="[438,604,387,411]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humboldti">
<emphasis box="[438,460,388,411]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[475,604,387,411]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">humboldti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in the “historical collection” portion of the Humboldt Universität holdings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[192,1440,483,539]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,483,507]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species is named both in honor of Alexander von Humboldt, the noted German naturalist and explorer, and the 
<collectingRegion box="[495,573,515,539]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Berlin</collectingRegion>
University that bears his name.
</paragraph>
